retail experience.

247
00:18:38,053 --> 00:18:42,410
'Cause human beings, we're tactile.
We like to touch the fruit before we buy.

248
00:18:42,493 --> 00:18:46,042
I can't believe you guys.
You're still using a catalog.

249
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:48,169
Now, these caskets here...

250
00:18:48,253 --> 00:18:50,813
that are on the upper level,
they appeal to men.

251
00:18:50,893 --> 00:18:54,329
It's at their average height.
Down below are the ladies' favorites.

252
00:18:54,413 --> 00:18:56,608
I have seen the future and this is it.

253
00:18:56,693 --> 00:18:59,810
-Dave, where would it go?
-We put it in the second viewing room.

254
00:18:59,893 --> 00:19:02,646
The one we use for storage?
It needs serious work.

255
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:04,803
So? We use this as a reason to do it!

256
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:08,249
Haven't we been planning to do that
with the money Mom gave us, anyway?

257
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,847
Dave, that money is almost all gone.

258
00:19:10,933 --> 00:19:13,731
A 2 by 5 like this will not break your back.

259
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,525
$21,500.

260
00:19:19,173 --> 00:19:22,529
I'll tell you what. $20,000, even.
That includes installation.

261
00:19:22,613 --> 00:19:25,650
I'll even throw in a fresh coat of paint
for your room.

262
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:27,325
You can't beat that with a stick.

263
00:19:27,413 --> 00:19:30,291
Nate, you always say
we have to spend money to make money.

264
00:19:30,373 --> 00:19:31,931
All right, how long to install?

265
00:19:32,013 --> 00:19:35,562
Give me the word,
and you'll be making sales in two days.

266
00:19:37,213 --> 00:19:39,647
-Do you really like it?
-Who wouldn't?

267
00:19:41,093 --> 00:19:42,651
I've never seen David happier.

268
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:45,531
It was like Christmas morning
when we were kids.

269
00:19:52,893 --> 00:19:55,123
Working out a little aggression there?

270
00:19:55,213 --> 00:19:58,922
We're having chicken piccata.
Have to marinate it overnight.

271
00:19:59,013 --> 00:20:02,369
You never cook like this for me.
You never even cook.

272
00:20:03,653 --> 00:20:07,282
And when Trevor goes back to New Haven,
I need you to forget that I can.

273
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:09,568
All right. What should I wear?

274
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:13,762
Speedo, hair extensions.
Wear what you want. I don't care.

275
00:20:14,053 --> 00:20:16,408
Don't wear one of your funeral suits.

276
00:20:16,493 --> 00:20:18,688
Oh, I thought you don't care.

277
00:20:19,293 --> 00:20:21,488
Wear something that makes you look...

278
00:20:21,573 --> 00:20:24,531
like the sexy bad boy you really are.

279
00:20:25,493 --> 00:20:29,850
Something that makes Mr. Wife-and-kids
question all of his middle-class choices.

280
00:20:29,933 --> 00:20:32,766
I'm all for that,
if you wear something low-cut in the back...

281
00:20:32,853 --> 00:20:35,651
so he can see my name
branded on your ass!

282
00:21:00,093 --> 00:21:01,287
Hello?

283
00:21:24,573 --> 00:21:26,370
New casket wall?

284
00:21:26,773 --> 00:21:29,571
You boys are doing better than I thought.

285
00:21:30,053 --> 00:21:32,965
-I'm Mitzi Dalton Huntley.
-David Fisher.

286
00:21:35,773 --> 00:21:38,003
Do you need to plan a funeral?

287
00:21:40,693 --> 00:21:43,127
You have no idea who I am, do you?

288
00:21:44,293 --> 00:21:48,525
I'm Southwest Regional Director
for Kroehner Services International.

289
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:51,088
I was hoping that maybe you
and your brother...

290
00:21:51,173 --> 00:21:53,687
might share a cup of coffee with me.

291
00:22:02,853 --> 00:22:06,004
Well, hello! Mitzi Dalton Huntley.

292
00:22:10,893 --> 00:22:12,690
You're a runner?

293
00:22:13,693 --> 00:22:15,604
It's bad for your knees.

294
00:22:15,693 --> 00:22:19,208
-Well, everything's bad for something.
-So I hear.

295
00:22:21,013 --> 00:22:22,651
Why are you here?

296
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:25,725
I made it clear to Matt Gilardi
we're not interested in selling.

297
00:22:25,813 --> 00:22:28,532
Matt Gilardi is no longer with Kroehner.

298
00:22:29,413 --> 00:22:31,529
Yup, I fired his worthless ass...

299
00:22:31,613 --> 00:22:34,889
because I didn't like the way
that he was representing our company.

300
00:22:34,973 --> 00:22:37,043
And that is why I'm here today.

301
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:39,647
To do a little damage control...

302
00:22:40,653 --> 00:22:42,689
and apologize to you boys.

303
00:22:42,973 --> 00:22:44,008
Right.

304
00:22:44,093 --> 00:22:48,564
I don't blame you for not trusting me.
Frankly, I'd be worried about you if you did.

305
00:22:48,653 --> 00:22:51,486
-Cream with three sugars.
-Thank you.

306
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:56,131
-You didn't put rat poison in here, did you?
-Drink it and find out.

307
00:22:59,013 --> 00:23:03,609
Oh, please! You boys aren't afraid
of Big Bad Mitzi, are you?

308
00:23:05,253 --> 00:23:08,290
Come on. The economy is in a tailspin.

309
00:23:08,733 --> 00:23:11,884
Corporations are downsizing, and resizing...

310
00:23:11,973 --> 00:23:14,328
and reorganizing, including Kroehner.

311
00:23:14,413 --> 00:23:17,564
We can't afford to take you over.
We've got problems of our own.

312
00:23:17,653 --> 00:23:21,487
-Okay, let's just cut the foreplay.
-But that's the best part.

313
00:23:21,653 --> 00:23:25,407
It's not that we don't trust you.
We despise everything you stand for:

314
00:23:25,493 --> 00:23:29,327
Corporate profits over personal service,
stockholders over clients.

315
00:23:29,453 --> 00:23:31,045
Greed over everything else.

316
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:35,365
I think you should take your gesture
of good faith and shove it up your ass!

317
00:23:36,493 --> 00:23:40,725
Well, that's one opinion.
Anything that you would care to add, David?

318
00:23:41,373 --> 00:23:44,649
No, I think Nate pretty much summed
our position up.

319
00:23:46,173 --> 00:23:48,050
Well, all righty then.

320
00:23:49,453 --> 00:23:51,489
I'll just show myself out.

321
00:23:55,093 --> 00:23:58,722
By the way, you might want to
clean out your coffeemaker.

322
00:23:58,813 --> 00:24:00,485
Your coffee sucks.

323
00:24:04,773 --> 00:24:06,365
This is not so good.

324
00:24:06,453 --> 00:24:08,489
Who the fuck is named Mitzi, anyway?

325
00:24:08,573 --> 00:24:12,009
That sounds like something
you name a fucking Chihuahua.

326
00:24:21,093 --> 00:24:22,890
Pretty bitching, huh?

327
00:24:23,813 --> 00:24:27,089
When did you start getting a pup tent
over caskets?

328
00:24:27,333 --> 00:24:30,609
-You're turning into David.
-Don't ever say that again.

329
00:24:31,333 --> 00:24:32,686
Very nice.

330
00:24:33,213 --> 00:24:36,364
Welcome to Casketeria.
May I take your order?

331
00:24:38,173 --> 00:24:41,483
So, Mr. Langmead is all ready to go.

332
00:24:41,893 --> 00:24:43,042
Great.

333
00:24:44,973 --> 00:24:49,205
So, Nate, have you guys had a chance
to think about what we.... You know.

334
00:24:51,093 --> 00:24:53,653
-Yeah, let's go into the office.
-Okay.

335
00:24:59,733 --> 00:25:03,089
So do these really open?
Can you hide shit in here?

336
00:25:04,093 --> 00:25:05,970
Can you close the door?

337
00:25:08,813 --> 00:25:11,452
"Close the door" doesn't sound too good.

338
00:25:15,573 --> 00:25:18,371
We can't give you a loan right now, Rico.

339
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:22,170
Look, we just spent a fortune
on the new casket wall.

340
00:25:22,253 --> 00:25:24,289
We got to maintain an emergency fund...

341
00:25:24,373 --> 00:25:28,366
in case Kroehner starts acting up again,
which suddenly looks very likely.

342
00:25:29,453 --> 00:25:31,842
It was a tough choice. I'm sorry.

343
00:25:32,973 --> 00:25:35,487
How much did that casket wall cost?

344
00:25:38,493 --> 00:25:40,848
Our first priority is keeping this house open.

345
00:25:40,933 --> 00:25:42,810
The more we make, the more you make.

346
00:25:42,893 --> 00:25:47,569
Tell me one thing. Did you and David decide
to buy that wall before or after we spoke?

347
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:57,005
First you won't make me a partner,
now you won't even...

348
00:25:57,093 --> 00:25:59,846
I've had it with you moping
about not being a partner.

349
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:04,051
It's not happening, all right?
I wish I could help you, but I can't.

350
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:08,524
I mean, fuck, we're your employer!
We're not a goddamn savings and loan!

351
00:26:14,653 --> 00:26:16,245
I'm sorry, Rico.

352
00:26:18,333 --> 00:26:21,564
If it were my money,
I'd give you all of it, you know that.

353
00:26:24,053 --> 00:26:26,806
Yeah, I'll pass it along to my kids.

354
00:26:28,413 --> 00:26:31,610
They have to play in a parking lot
next to a dumpster.

355
00:26:39,453 --> 00:26:40,568
Fuck.

356
00:27:05,173 --> 00:27:06,526
I'm scared.

357
00:27:09,053 --> 00:27:13,046
-What's gonna happen to me now?
-Well, that's not my problem, pal.

358
00:27:20,093 --> 00:27:21,208
What?

359
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:24,843
I was so young. Why me?

360
00:27:25,173 --> 00:27:28,324
Why the fuck not you?
What did you think, you were immune?

361
00:27:28,413 --> 00:27:32,770
Everybody dies. Everybody!
What makes you so fucking special?

362
00:27:47,253 --> 00:27:48,925
What do you think?

363
00:27:49,013 --> 00:27:52,801
-I'm not signing up for anything.
-I'm not selling anything.

364
00:27:53,093 --> 00:27:55,323
I'm a visitor, just like you.

365
00:27:56,533 --> 00:27:58,410
Do you know how you can tell?

366
00:27:58,493 --> 00:28:02,042
-The Elevated wear plastic tags.
-The Elevated?

367
00:28:02,133 --> 00:28:03,964
You'll learn the lingo.

368
00:28:04,053 --> 00:28:07,443
My daughter is graduating today. You?

369
00:28:07,893 --> 00:28:10,407
My business associate is graduating.

370
00:28:11,133 --> 00:28:15,046
-So what exactly is this?
-I don't know for sure myself.

371
00:28:15,733 --> 00:28:18,293
But Sheila has never been happier.

372
00:28:18,533 --> 00:28:21,286
So I wanted to see what it was all about.

373
00:28:21,573 --> 00:28:23,245
Let's get started.

374
00:28:23,653 --> 00:28:27,248
Today just might be
the most important day of your lives.

375
00:28:27,333 --> 00:28:30,245
Come sit with me.
There's safety in numbers.

376
00:28:32,973 --> 00:28:35,328
You cannot design a life that works...

377
00:28:35,413 --> 00:28:38,246
without first drafting a clear blueprint.

378
00:28:38,773 --> 00:28:42,049
And you cannot construct a life
that has meaning...

379
00:28:42,373 --> 00:28:45,171
without first laying a solid foundation.

380
00:28:45,613 --> 00:28:48,730
You are the architect of your life.

381
00:28:49,533 --> 00:28:52,172
Not your emotionally distant father...

382
00:28:52,253 --> 00:28:54,687
not your overly critical mother...

383
00:28:55,413 --> 00:28:58,086
not your petty, fair-weather friends.

384
00:28:59,893 --> 00:29:01,008
You.

385
00:29:09,733 --> 00:29:12,964
It was hard
the first time I stood up for myself.

386
00:29:14,773 --> 00:29:17,367
I always wanted everybody to like me.

387
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:21,210
Even though I hated myself,
you had to like me.

388
00:29:21,853 --> 00:29:24,208
When I rebuilt my foundation...

389
00:29:24,893 --> 00:29:28,932
and I was able to honor
and elevate the better part of me...

390
00:29:29,253 --> 00:29:31,767
I realized I really like me.

391
00:29:33,413 --> 00:29:35,210
So you don't have to.

392
00:29:39,933 --> 00:29:41,924
I'm not a salvage job...

393
00:29:42,613 --> 00:29:45,127
I am not a teardown, I am not junk.

394
00:29:46,853 --> 00:29:50,163
It's taken me many years to say that,
to believe it.

395
00:29:51,453 --> 00:29:55,002
There are days that I slip,
and I treat people like shit.

396
00:29:57,013 --> 00:29:59,925
Like I treated myself for the last 30 years.

397
00:30:01,053 --> 00:30:03,806
But, damn it, I swear I'm going to win this.

398
00:30:04,173 --> 00:30:06,767
I'm going to build the life...

399
00:30:08,213 --> 00:30:10,443
that I always wanted to live.

400
00:30:13,693 --> 00:30:14,762
Okay.

401
00:30:20,173 --> 00:30:22,243
I thought it was too late.

402
00:30:23,373 --> 00:30:25,364
Two terrible marriages...

403
00:30:25,653 --> 00:30:30,204
children who won't even
return my phone calls.

404
00:30:31,253 --> 00:30:35,565
It hurts. I'm 41 and I feel like I'm 80.

405
00:30:36,933 --> 00:30:38,571
But I have value.

406
00:30:40,253 --> 00:30:41,845
I'm still here.

407
00:30:42,893 --> 00:30:45,805
And as long as I believe in myself...

408
00:30:46,333 --> 00:30:49,052
and speak fiercely from the "I"...

409
00:30:49,493 --> 00:30:51,529
then there's still hope.

410
00:30:52,093 --> 00:30:56,132
There's no mortgage on my life. I own it.

411
00:30:58,853 --> 00:31:00,411
Thank you, Mom.

412
00:31:06,453 --> 00:31:07,852
Thank you.

413
00:31:30,133 --> 00:31:34,206
That was humiliating.
As if my self-esteem wasn't low enough.

414
00:31:34,973 --> 00:31:38,124
It's kind of funny.
All that time we were racquetball partners...

415
00:31:38,213 --> 00:31:40,169
we actually never played racquetball.

416
00:31:40,253 --> 00:31:44,132
I am serious about learning how to play.
Are you available Thursday afternoon?

417
00:31:44,213 --> 00:31:45,931
I don't know. I'll check.

418
00:31:48,093 --> 00:31:51,768
Want to drop by my niece's birthday party
later? Eddie's on call.

419
00:31:51,933 --> 00:31:53,048
Sure.

420
00:31:53,133 --> 00:31:57,012
