00:35:45,173 --> 00:35:49,689
who insisted that it was the perfect profile
of a classic borderline personality.

480
00:35:51,453 --> 00:35:53,762
You've heard that before, right?

481
00:35:53,933 --> 00:35:57,050
I actually went to the library,
and looked up the symptoms...

482
00:35:57,133 --> 00:35:59,693
and started behaving like that
to fuck with them.

483
00:35:59,773 --> 00:36:02,492
Seriously? That's brilliant.

484
00:36:03,093 --> 00:36:06,449
-How old were you?
-I must have been 9 or 10.

485
00:36:06,933 --> 00:36:10,528
-It was towards the end.
-Personally, I think it's a crock of shit.

486
00:36:10,613 --> 00:36:13,685
Did you ever notice how the majority
of borderlines are women?

487
00:36:13,773 --> 00:36:17,482
I see it as just a misogynistic attempt
to pathologize women...

488
00:36:17,573 --> 00:36:20,292
who refuse to toe the patriarchal line.

489
00:36:21,693 --> 00:36:25,925
Yeah, I spent six months in Seattle
on a teaching fellowship.

490
00:36:26,333 --> 00:36:29,131
-Ever do any climbing there?
-Yeah, some bouldering.

491
00:36:29,213 --> 00:36:31,568
No real climbing with ropes, but....

492
00:36:32,053 --> 00:36:33,805
Were you a cragger?

493
00:36:34,253 --> 00:36:37,165
Rank amateur urban kind, but I do love it.

494
00:36:37,813 --> 00:36:40,611
-You done the U.W. climbing rock?
-That's where I learned.

495
00:36:40,693 --> 00:36:43,810
I never knew 30 feet
was so high off the ground.

496
00:36:44,093 --> 00:36:47,244
30 feet? That's nothing.
I've got a couple of buddies...

497
00:36:47,333 --> 00:36:50,723
they're real thrill seekers.
I mean, they climb high.

498
00:36:50,853 --> 00:36:52,889
But no way I can do that.

499
00:36:54,653 --> 00:36:57,611
Got to think about
more than just myself now.

500
00:37:03,573 --> 00:37:05,211
Bren looks great.

501
00:37:06,973 --> 00:37:09,771
-How's she doing?
-She's doing great.

502
00:37:10,413 --> 00:37:13,211
-Man, she is so fucking smart.
-Yes, she is.

503
00:37:13,293 --> 00:37:16,444
She used to run circles around me,
I can tell you that.

504
00:37:17,613 --> 00:37:20,605
Everybody expected
such great things from her.

505
00:37:24,333 --> 00:37:26,005
How's her brother?

506
00:37:27,693 --> 00:37:30,002
He's in the hospital right now.

507
00:37:43,573 --> 00:37:45,723
I just wanted to get out of my head.

508
00:37:45,813 --> 00:37:50,091
So I took 18 months of classes and
I went to the Shiatsu Institute thinking...

509
00:37:50,173 --> 00:37:53,210
I'd do it until I figure out
what I really want to do.

510
00:37:53,293 --> 00:37:55,648
And here we are, 10 years later.

511
00:37:56,093 --> 00:37:58,288
-But you love what you do, right?
-I do.

512
00:37:58,373 --> 00:38:02,332
That's the key. And you know what?
There is this girl in my health club.

513
00:38:02,413 --> 00:38:06,406
She doesn't do shiatsu, but I swear,
she is gifted.

514
00:38:06,493 --> 00:38:07,687
Gifted.

515
00:38:08,813 --> 00:38:11,247
You know, there is a science to shiatsu.

516
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:14,245
Chinese medicine dates back
over 2,000 years.

517
00:38:18,413 --> 00:38:21,644
This is delicious, Brenda.
You know, I never cook like this.

518
00:38:21,733 --> 00:38:23,610
I can make pasta, but that's about it.

519
00:38:23,693 --> 00:38:27,606
She's got me beat, though.
I can make toast and ice cubes.

520
00:38:28,093 --> 00:38:32,052
-Nate does pretty good microwave popcorn.
-What do you do, Nate?

521
00:38:33,293 --> 00:38:35,204
I'm a funeral director.

522
00:38:37,533 --> 00:38:38,761
Really?

523
00:38:43,653 --> 00:38:46,884
What makes one decide
to become a funeral director?

524
00:38:48,493 --> 00:38:51,007
Well, I was born into it, actually.

525
00:38:52,053 --> 00:38:54,123
Like being born into the Mafia.

526
00:39:03,853 --> 00:39:06,811
Not so fast there, hotshot. It's a toll road.

527
00:39:31,013 --> 00:39:32,332
Time out.

528
00:39:32,413 --> 00:39:36,088
Sometimes he becomes completely irrational
just to get attention.

529
00:39:37,613 --> 00:39:39,365
Sometimes I do that.

530
00:39:48,573 --> 00:39:52,282
-Uncle K.
-Hey, baby girl. Happy birthday.

531
00:39:53,053 --> 00:39:54,122
I'm nine.

532
00:39:54,213 --> 00:39:57,011
I guess that means
I can't call you "baby girl" anymore.

533
00:39:57,093 --> 00:40:00,483
-You better not.
-This is my friend David.

534
00:40:00,853 --> 00:40:03,083
-Hi there.
-Hi.

535
00:40:03,253 --> 00:40:05,084
So where's the party?

536
00:40:24,133 --> 00:40:26,169
You want some? It's good.

537
00:40:27,933 --> 00:40:30,083
This is for you, sweetheart.

538
00:40:37,333 --> 00:40:40,769
-I saw this in the store.
-I can't believe they still make these.

539
00:40:40,853 --> 00:40:43,731
-I thought you'd like it.
-Thanks, Uncle K.

540
00:40:48,173 --> 00:40:51,006
-Where's Mommy?
-In the bedroom, sleeping.

541
00:40:52,293 --> 00:40:55,365
-I'm going to go and talk to her for a bit.
-Okay.

542
00:41:30,373 --> 00:41:35,003
-Hi. Thought you wasn't coming till later.
-It is later.

543
00:41:35,893 --> 00:41:38,726
What happened to Taylor's birthday party?

544
00:41:38,893 --> 00:41:40,042
Shit.

545
00:41:41,453 --> 00:41:44,251
I got home from work and was bone-tired.

546
00:41:44,453 --> 00:41:47,650
I'll take her to a flea market
over the weekend, get her something.

547
00:41:47,733 --> 00:41:50,850
That's all you did for her birthday?
Buy her an Entenmann's cake?

548
00:41:50,933 --> 00:41:52,605
It's her favorite.

549
00:41:57,773 --> 00:42:01,607
-What are you on? Don't lie to me!
-I ain't on nothing, okay?

550
00:42:01,773 --> 00:42:04,082
You think I'm suicidal or just plain stupid?

551
00:42:04,173 --> 00:42:08,052
You need to stop living for yourself
and start thinking about that little girl!

552
00:42:08,133 --> 00:42:11,967
I am seven months clean.
I work two jobs and take care of my kid.

553
00:42:12,053 --> 00:42:15,443
I forgot her motherfucking birthday.
Do you want to arrest me for that?

554
00:42:15,533 --> 00:42:18,730
You can do all the damage you want
to yourself. I can't stop that!

555
00:42:18,813 --> 00:42:21,725
But I'm not gonna let you fuck up her life!

556
00:42:21,813 --> 00:42:23,326
Take your hands off me.

557
00:42:23,413 --> 00:42:26,928
I will file an assault charge
and you do not want that.

558
00:42:32,693 --> 00:42:36,572
My sister had one of these
when she was a kid. But I broke it.

559
00:42:36,813 --> 00:42:39,008
-On purpose?
-No.

560
00:42:39,453 --> 00:42:41,205
I wanted to make a pizza...

561
00:42:41,293 --> 00:42:44,888
and I put in a 300-watt bulb,
and the whole thing melted.

562
00:42:45,533 --> 00:42:48,969
-That's dumb.
-Yeah, I know. I was 17.

563
00:42:50,773 --> 00:42:52,923
You don't give a fuck about her!

564
00:42:53,933 --> 00:42:56,288
-I'm talking to you!
-You don't know shit.

565
00:42:56,373 --> 00:42:58,170
Get the fuck out of my house!

566
00:42:58,973 --> 00:43:01,646
-Do you live in a house?
-Yup.

567
00:43:03,053 --> 00:43:05,726
-A big house?
-Not that big.

568
00:43:08,893 --> 00:43:10,246
Got a daddy?

569
00:43:11,493 --> 00:43:12,846
I used to.

570
00:43:20,453 --> 00:43:22,648
-We got to go, okay?
-Okay.

571
00:43:22,733 --> 00:43:26,282
All right, listen, I'll come back tomorrow...

572
00:43:26,693 --> 00:43:30,049
as soon as I get off work
and we'll go to the movies, okay?

573
00:43:30,133 --> 00:43:31,282
Okay.

574
00:43:39,173 --> 00:43:40,572
We got to go.

575
00:43:51,893 --> 00:43:53,212
Oh, my God.

576
00:43:54,253 --> 00:43:55,845
What was I thinking?

577
00:43:56,653 --> 00:43:58,848
Well, I was only 19.

578
00:43:59,733 --> 00:44:01,689
Come on, it wasn't that bad.

579
00:44:02,653 --> 00:44:06,692
"There is this girl at my health club.
She is gifted. "

580
00:44:08,973 --> 00:44:10,406
What a dork!

581
00:44:10,733 --> 00:44:13,884
-His ears were filthy. Did you notice that?
-No.

582
00:44:14,173 --> 00:44:17,290
-Now, her, I liked.
-That kid, what a freak.

583
00:44:18,973 --> 00:44:21,646
They should start saving up
for therapy now.

584
00:44:22,493 --> 00:44:25,724
We need some friends,
some couples we don't hate.

585
00:44:26,453 --> 00:44:28,045
We have each other.

586
00:44:32,173 --> 00:44:34,812
Maybe we should volunteer someplace.

587
00:44:36,053 --> 00:44:37,691
No, I'm serious.

588
00:44:38,853 --> 00:44:43,324
Do something good for the world.
Needle exchange program.

589
00:44:44,653 --> 00:44:47,372
Habitat for Humanity, Meals on Wheels.

590
00:44:47,773 --> 00:44:50,685
Just give more, consume less.

591
00:44:52,853 --> 00:44:55,447
-Brenda, I'm dying.
-What?

592
00:44:57,133 --> 00:45:00,921
-What did you say?
-After the auto accident, I had...

593
00:45:01,893 --> 00:45:04,361
x-rays, MRls, and they found something.

594
00:45:05,973 --> 00:45:09,761
It's called AVM. I think I'm gonna die from it.
I don't know when.

595
00:45:14,733 --> 00:45:16,325
I'm so scared.

596
00:45:22,693 --> 00:45:25,048
-Are you listening to me?
-Yeah.

597
00:45:26,533 --> 00:45:30,208
Meals on Wheels.
You really want to do that?

598
00:45:31,693 --> 00:45:36,084
I don't know. I have to do something.
I hate my fucking life.

599
00:45:36,853 --> 00:45:38,411
What's wrong?

600
00:45:38,773 --> 00:45:41,651
I was watching Trevor and Dawn tonight...

601
00:45:43,453 --> 00:45:45,409
thinking they're just...

602
00:45:45,973 --> 00:45:47,964
so complete.

603
00:45:49,373 --> 00:45:52,922
They have something
that I will never have, ever.

604
00:45:53,613 --> 00:45:57,322
Either I wasn't born with it,
or it was beaten out of me...

605
00:45:57,413 --> 00:46:01,372
or maybe I made myself
into a self-fulfilling prophecy...

606
00:46:01,453 --> 00:46:05,605
and I really am a borderline personality.
Now, wouldn't that be ironic?

607
00:46:07,373 --> 00:46:09,409
What's going on with you?

608
00:46:11,773 --> 00:46:13,252
I don't know.

609
00:46:14,493 --> 00:46:17,291
I spent my childhood
performing for clinicians...

610
00:46:17,373 --> 00:46:20,410
the rest of my life taking care
of my train wreck of a brother...

611
00:46:20,493 --> 00:46:23,212
and I have no idea who I am.

612
00:46:27,533 --> 00:46:30,047
I'm gonna make a cup of tea. You want one?

613
00:46:32,093 --> 00:46:33,446
No, thanks.

614
00:46:44,613 --> 00:46:47,411
God, I can't wait until our next funeral.

615
00:46:48,093 --> 00:46:51,972
-What do you think, Mom?
-It's very modern.

616
00:46:52,213 --> 00:46:55,285
We figure it'll pay for itself
in less than eight months.

617
00:46:55,373 --> 00:46:57,409
What did we spend on this?

618
00:46:59,133 --> 00:47:00,964
About $20,000.

619
00:47:02,373 --> 00:47:05,490
How much is left
in the reserve fund I gave you?

620
00:47:05,573 --> 00:47:06,847
I'll have to check.

621
00:47:06,933 --> 00:47:10,164
I want a full accounting
of how you spent that $93,000.

622
00:47:10,253 --> 00:47:14,531
I'm an investor in Fisher & Sons. That wall's
part of my investment. I expect a return.

623
00:47:14,613 --> 00:47:16,092
Of course, Mom.

624
00:47:16,173 --> 00:47:18,926
I am speaking fiercely from the "I"!

625
00:47:20,053 --> 00:47:21,452
Do you mind?

626
00:47:26,213 --> 00:47:27,692
I don't know.

627
00:47:27,773 --> 00:47:31,607
I just need one of you to sign right here,
and we'll be done.

628
00:47:31,813 --> 00:47:35,408
Do we need to write you a check now,
or can we mail it to your office?

629
00:47:35,493 --> 00:47:38,007
You might want to open this first.

630
00:47:39,613 --> 00:47:41,251
Came out good, huh?

631
00:47:41,333 --> 00:47:43,483
-It's beautiful.
-It's great.

632
00:47:47,693 --> 00:47:52,005
"Enjoy the new casket wall. It's on me.
Kisses. Mitzi Dalton Huntley. "

633
00:47:53,013 --> 00:47:55,732
-Why would she pay for our wall?
-She didn't pay for it.

634
00:47:55,813 --> 00:47:58,452
Appleby Caskets is owned by Kroehner.

635
00:47:59,213 --> 00:48:01,727
-Since when?
-Since three weeks ago.

636
00:48:02,893 --> 00:48:04,087
Enjoy.

637
00:48:08,373 --> 00:48:12,685
-She has us selling Kroehner caskets.
-Wow. She's good.

638
00:48:14,013 --> 00:48:16,891
I guess we can at least help out Rico now.

639
00:48:17,213 --> 00:48:18,851
That's a good idea.

640
00:48:19,213 --> 00:48:22,011
Then we go under,
he's out of work and can't pay us back.

641
00:48:22,093 --> 00:48:24,288
Which won't matter
as we won't exist anymore.

642
00:48:24,373 --> 00:48:26,762
David, we just saved $20,000.

643
00:48:27,413 --> 00:48:30,610
We didn't save $20,000.
We just didn't spend it.

644
00:48:31,133 --> 00:48:34,682
Actually, we just lost $1,600,
because we had to give the Langmeads...

645
00:48:34,773 --> 00:48:38,083
the Haven Four for an even $10,000,
thank you very much.

646
00:48:47,213 --> 00:48:49,647
Honey, of course I love the house.

647
00:48:49,733 --> 00:48:52,327
Believe me,
they are never gonna give us the money.

648
00:48:52,413 --> 00:48:56,611
-You love the house, though.
-We just have to keep on looking, baby.

649
00:48:56,813 --> 00:49:00,442
We don't. I went to the realtor this morning
and we got the house.

650
00:49:00,533 --> 00:49:04,082
I wrote a check for the down payment,
and now Julio can have his own room.

651
00:49:04,173 --> 00:49:07,483
What? Where did you get the money?
What do you mean?

652
00:49:08,093 --> 00:49:09,845
Okay, don't be mad.

653
00:49:20,373 --> 00:49:23,968
You went behind my back and asked
your sister for the money? Are you crazy?

654
00:49:24,053 --> 00:49:28,012
-Rico, I wasn't about to lose that house.
-I provide for this family, not her!

655
00:49:28,093 --> 00:49:31,802
I'm gone eight to ten hours a day
missing my kids, to get us what we need.

656
00:49:31,893 --> 00:49:33,690
I don't need her fucking handouts!

657
00:49:33,773 --> 00:49:37,368
Please, I don't want to hear
any machismo bullshit today, okay?

658
00:49:39,653 --> 00:49:41,564
What did you say to me?

659
00:49:48,093 --> 00:49:49,890
Baby, we have a house.

660
00:49:50,413 --> 00:49:54,042
It's our first house. Can you be happy?

661
00:49:55,813 --> 00:49:58,566
-I'm canceling that check.
-Listen to me.

662
00:49:58,773 --> 00:50:02,209
When the transmission went last month,
where did the money come from?

663
00:50:02,293 --> 00:50:06,002
When I chipped my tooth and
we couldn't afford the dentist, who paid?

664
00:50:06,093 --> 00:50:09,768
Angelica's doing good.
She has extra money. She's family.

665
00:50:10,053 --> 00:50:12,613
She loves us. She wants to help us.

666
00:50:14,653 --> 00:50:16,086
So, please...

667
00:50:17,933 --> 00:50:19,651
put down the phone.

668
00:50:30,133 --> 00:50:31,771
We have a house.

669
00:50:36,173 --> 00:50:37,925
Everything is good.

670
00:50:54,493 --> 00:50:56,643
I haven't seen you all day.

671
00:50:57,813 --> 00:50:59,212
How's Andy?

672
00:51:01,333 --> 00:51:03,210
He's gonna be okay.

673
00:51:04,573 --> 00:51:06,211
What was he on?

674
00:51:07,093 --> 00:51:09,687
Some weird shit. I don't really know.

675
00:51:10,133 --> 00:51:14,206
Because I heard that he smoked a joint
dipped in embalming fluid.

676
00:51:16,653 --> 00:51:17,768
I wouldn't know.

677
00:51:17,853 --> 00:51:21,607
That wouldn't be embalming fluid
that you stole from my house, right?

678
00:51:22,653 --> 00:51:25,008
What the fuck is wrong with you?

679
00:51:25,093 --> 00:51:28,051
Do you have any idea
how much trouble this could get us in?

680
00:51:28,133 --> 00:51:29,691
He could have died.

681
00:51:29,773 --> 00:51:33,686
And my brothers could be getting
a phone call from the cops right now, okay?

682
00:51:33,773 --> 00:51:36,731
-And you're gonna bring this on my...
-Would you stop?

683
00:51:38,533 --> 00:51:42,765
Look, I gave Andy five fry sticks to sell,
and he fucking smoked them all.

684
00:51:43,213 --> 00:51:45,727
I am sorry that I fucked with you.

685
00:51:46,253 --> 00:51:49,643
But you took me down there,
and I saw the stuff and I wasn't thinking.

686
00:51:49,733 --> 00:51:53,043
You were thinking.
You were thinking about yourself!

687
00:51:53,653 --> 00:51:56,213
Claire, listen to me. Look.

688
00:51:57,053 --> 00:52:01,683
The cops have a videotape of me, Andy,
and Dink robbing a convenience store...

689
00:52:01,773 --> 00:52:04,970
and now I'm worried
that Andy's gonna turn me in.

690
00:52:09,133 --> 00:52:10,964
Who the fuck are you?

691
00:52:14,053 --> 00:52:17,807
Fuck! Everything I touch turns to shit.

692
00:52:21,413 --> 00:52:23,210
Everything is shit.

693
00:52:25,813 --> 00:52:28,043
Everybody was right about you.

694
00:52:29,893 --> 00:52:33,886
You are the only good thing that I have left.
Please don't give up on me.

695
00:52:36,293 --> 00:52:37,487
Please.

696
00:52:43,333 --> 00:52:44,402
No.

697
00:53:10,533 --> 00:53:11,932
Oh, Christ!

698
00:53:13,773 --> 00:53:16,970
You know,
you're really starting to piss me off.

699
00:53:17,893 --> 00:53:20,407
What? What the fuck do you want from me?

700
00:53:20,493 --> 00:53:24,406
I want you to see me! Look at me!

701
00:53:43,093 --> 00:53:44,492
Look at me.

702
00:53:56,493 --> 00:53:58,290
That's more like it.

703
00:54:27,333 --> 00:54:30,689
-You done with your run already?
-I didn't need it.

704
00:54:31,573 --> 00:54:34,849
The Langmead viewing is at 6:00.
Are you ready? If you're not...

705
00:54:34,933 --> 00:54:37,401
Dave, I need to tell you something.

706
00:54:38,053 --> 00:54:39,930
What have you done now?

707
00:54:45,253 --> 00:54:47,323
I think we should sit down.

708
00:54:57,253 --> 00:54:58,652
What is it?

709
00:55:06,173 --> 00:55:09,927
Listen, if I've been a real dick or something,
I'm really sorry about it.

710
00:55:12,853 --> 00:55:16,766
I found out that I have a condition
called AVM...

711
00:55:20,853 --> 00:55:25,290
which basically means I could have
a stroke or aneurysm at just about any time.

712
00:55:28,773 --> 00:55:31,207
I'm not coping with this very well.

713
00:55:33,893 --> 00:55:37,090
I don't know how to deal,
and I don't know what to do.

714
00:55:44,293 --> 00:55:45,851
Oh, fuck.

715
00:56:55,093 --> 00:56:56,321
English

